post_text: Steuben All-County at Bath is well underway! The 6th Grade Band, under the direction of Mrs. Amy Harpster from Corning-Painted Post Middle School, the Jr. High Chorus, under the direction of Mr. Lon Beery from Spry Middle School (Webster CSD), and the Sr. High Band, under the direction of Mr. Shawn Halquist, from Brockport High School. It is going to be a great weekend of music making for our students! Join us for a concert performance, tomorrow, Saturday, March 23, 2019 in the Haverling High School Auditorium. Tickets are $4.00/person and can be purchased at the door. Concert begins at 2:00pm!

shared_text:
Haverling Rams Athletics
October 28, 2018 at 10:06 AM ·

The state qualifier game for boys soccer is now set for Tuesday night at Avon High School. Game time is set for 7:00pm. The Rams will take on the Class B1 champions, Pal-Mac.

For students in grades 7-12 that are interested in riding a spectator bus, You need to be signed up with a permission slip and $5 turned into your respective office by Tuesday at noon so we know wether or not we have enough for the bus.

In order to be a little more efficient, parents can send in a written permission slip with $5 tomorrow (Monday) as compared to waiting to get the printed up permission slips from the office. Or you print out the slip that appears with this post.

Only current Haverling students in grades 7-12 can ride the spectator bus. Due to insurance regulations, parents or adult fans are not able to ride the bus.

post_text:
Attention 7-12 Band Parents! (for next school year)

Band Trip Parent Meeting

There is an important meeting for any student, along with at least one of their parents or guardians, that is even slightly interested in next year’s student band trip to Nashville, Tennessee.

This looks to be an exciting overnight trip to learn, experience, and enjoy the city called Music City, USA!

The meeting will share information about the dates and itinerary, as well as the registration process, trip costs, and payment procedures.

The meeting is being held on Tuesday, June 5th in the high school room 450, at 7:00pm.

Haverling Rams Athletics
March 28, 2018 at 2:18 PM ·

Our Haverling family recently lost one of our largest supporters. Mrs. Shirley Hill has been the face of the soccer complex concession stand for decades.

Calling hours will be Friday, March 30th at Fagan's Funeral Home from Noon-3PM and 5PM-7PM. The funeral service will be held Saturday, March 31st at 11AM at the St. Thomas Episcopal Church in Bath. A Celebration of Life will be held immediately following the service at the Pleasant Valley Wine Company in Hammondsport.

post_text: Last week was a busy week for our musicians! On Tuesday the 3rd Grade Chorus had an outstanding concert and on Wednesday the 4th Grade Choir, 5/6 Choir, and the 5/6 Band filled the auditorium with great music! The Chamber Choir performed for the National Association of Retired Federal Employees, Rotary, Steuben County Office Building, and along with the 3rd Grade Chorus performed at the Board of Education meeting. We hope you can join us for the concert on Tuesday featuring the 7/8 Choir and Band!

post_text: Congratulations to these high Schools singers and instrumentalists who participated in the 2015 NYSSMA Sr. High Area All-State in Corning this past weekend. Each of these students were in either the Mixed Chorus, Women's Chorus, String Orchestra, or Concert Band. A special shout out to Olivia Snavely who was selected to perform as a soloist in one of the Women's Chorus selections!

post_text: High school students Lydia Arnts, Colton Green, Luke Snavely, and Olivia Snavely sang the National Anthem and Trumpeter Josh Abrams played Taps for the annual Prisoner of War/Missing in Action National Day of Recognition Ceremony held at the Bath VA on Friday, September 18. We are grateful for their contribution to this ceremony and to their local community!

post_text:
Haverling Music Department is incredibly proud to announce that three superb musicians will be representing our district at the New York State School Music Association All-State! These students auditioned for the honor last April and were notified recently of their acceptance.

Senior Luke Snavely will sing as a tenor in the All-State Mixed Chorus

Junior Lydia Arnts will play clarinet in the All-State Symphonic Band

Junior Olivia Snavely will sing as a soprano in the All-State Women's Chorus

These fine young musicians will join 890 other students from New York State in December to rehearse and perform a concert in the prestigious Eastman Theater, Rochester, NY.
